Officers of the Nigeria Police Force, Edo State command have laid siege on some protesters kicking against the current hike in the pump price of petrol and the price of cement per bag. The police stopped the protesters at the main gate/entrance of the king square roundabout close to the palace of the Oba of Benin in ring-road. Details later… Group condemns arrest of journalists, protesters in Lagos Fuel price: ​Strike is the only way to express our grievance - Labour leader RevolutionNow group, students protest electricity, petrol, DSTV hike in Osun